House Resolution 612
By: Representatives Scott of the 76th, Davis of the 87th, and Schofield of the 63rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Kenneth K. Mickens; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Kenneth K. Mickens; and
4 WHEREAS, Kenneth K. Mickens was born on April 3, 1955, in Havana, Florida, a beloved
5 son of Arthur Mickens Sr. and Ella Mae Harrison-Mickens; and
6 WHEREAS, he served as a guardian of this nation's freedom and liberty with the United
7 States Army, valiantly and courageously protecting his fellow Americans; and
8 WHEREAS, Mr. Mickens began a career at the Tallahassee FCI as a correctional officer and
9 later followed his passion on becoming an entrepreneur, creating fashion shows, the
10 Commonwealth Tax Services, X-Men Builder and Associates, and the Frankie and Johnny
11 clothing store; and
12 WHEREAS, a man of deep and abiding faith, Mr. Mickens was an active member of New
13 Mt. Zion AME Church; and
